  "disclaimer": "Monitoring alert only; no risk acceptance, breach waiver, limit or appetite change, risk- or control-rating change, incident or case closure, regulatory filing, or system-of-record change has been made or recommended. KRI exceptions require human risk review and adjudication.",
  "narrative": "Scheduled KRI monitoring run krim-2026-07-17-0001 (as of 2026-07-17) evaluated 7 Key Risk Indicators against their versioned appetite thresholds (kri-cfg-2026.07) and raised 9 alerts (8 new, 1 already open and deduplicated). Two critical KRIs are in red-limit breach and routed to the risk committee for adjudication: the failed payment processing rate reached 3.5% against a 3.0% limit (already open; linked to incident INC-2026-0142) and the Liquidity Coverage Ratio fell to 102% against a 105% floor. The retail 90+ day delinquency rate sits at 4.5% in the amber band and has deteriorated for three consecutive months, raising a threshold warning and an adverse-trend warning on the watchlist. Critical third-party SLA misses are within absolute appetite (4 vs a 5 limit) but run at twice the seasonally-expected level, so a seasonal-deviation alert is queued for review. The upheld-complaints KRI has no reported value this period, so a data-quality alert is queued rather than a false all-clear. Market-risk VaR utilization is 88% (amber) but its observation is 12 days stale against a 5-day limit, so both its threshold warning and a freshness alert are flagged stale_input and treated as low-confidence pending a refreshed feed. Staff attrition remains within appetite and raised no alert. All items are routed to the named risk queues for human review; severity and queue are deterministic. Monitoring alert only; no risk acceptance, breach waiver, limit or appetite change, risk- or control-rating change, incident or case closure, regulatory filing, or system-of-record change has been made or recommended. KRI exceptions require human risk review and adjudication.",
  "notes": "Thresholds, directions, and seasonal baselines are versioned configuration (kri-cfg-2026.07); no per-metric tuning. Severity and queue are deterministic. Linked incident INC-2026-0142 is context only; this monitor does not create, modify, or dispose of incidents or cases."
